blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Nwad Piplup, Buneary, Pachirisu, Togekiss, Mamoswine and Quilava fusion Fairy/Fire Type Ability: Huge Power The Protection...
caption:
Nwad

Piplup, Buneary, Pachirisu, Togekiss, Mamoswine and Quilava fusion

Fairy/Fire Type

Ability: Huge Power

The Protection Pokemon

Pokemon Trainer Dawn was travelling through a new region searching for a contest hall when she slipped from a cliff.  When Dawn’s pokemon saw that she was in trouble, they used the power of fusion to combine their powers and help save her.  Though it has wings, it uses them for speed, rather than flight.  Nwad is rather hot-headed and will charge head on into a battle or contest.  

Request for anon. I hope you like it.  It was difficult to combine them all as they all have different body types so it’s kinda an abomination.

summary: SM091 - It's an Outbreak-chu! The Pikachu Valley!! Full Summary and VA cast!
title: SM091 - It's an Outbreak-chu! The Pikachu Valley!! Full Summary and VA cast!
body:
Starting today (Sunday Oct 7th), the show is switching timeslot to Sunday at 6pm! Satoshi has gone to the “Pikachu Valley”, which is full of Pikachu. There’s all kinds of Pikachu there, and…
Also, we get Nicole Fujita’s first ever attempt at voice acting!

Summary:
Starting today (Sunday Oct 7th), the show is switching timeslot to Sunday at 6pm! Satoshi and the others have gone to the “Pikachu Valley”, where lots of Pikachu live. There, they meet a slightly eccentric woman that really loves Pikachu. The Pikachu in the valley come in all shapes and forms, which Satoshi’s Pikachu seems to find amusing as well! But then the Rocket Gang shows up and attempt to get all the Pikachu, running completely wild with Mimikkyu’s Z-Move! What will happen now?!
Kurin-chan, who’s played by Nicole Fujita, appears in the episode as well!

Voice Cast:
Rica Matsumoto: Satoshi
Ikue Ohtani: Pikachu
Daisuke Namikawa: Rotom
Kaito Ishikawa: Kaki
Megumi Hayashibara: Musashi
Shinichiro Miki: Kojiro

Nicole Fujita: Kurin

summary: In the Burned Tower in Johto, a houndour was spotted lying in the entrance of the building. Most people kept away from it though...
body:
In the Burned Tower in Johto, a houndour was spotted lying in the entrance of the building. Most people kept away from it though due to it’s odd appearances.

Three houndour pups, or rather one with three heads. It has been concluded they were simply conjoined triplets, but those in the town saw it as a bad omen

summary:
Ranuki and Tancoon- the nature spirit pokemon 
Ranuki- the nature spirit pokemon
Type: dark grass | ability: pickpocket 
This...
body:
Ranuki and Tancoon- the nature spirit pokemon

Ranuki- the nature spirit pokemon

Type: dark grass | ability: pickpocket

This pokemon is known to be quite the thief. It steals items from people and pokemon all the time and is often considered a pest. They can often be found fighting or playing with a tancoon.

Tancoon- the nature spirit pokemon

Type: fairy grass | ability: friend guard

This pokemon is known to give out list items it finds to trainers it thinks are trustworthy. People find this pokemon adorable. It can often be found in the company of a ranuki.

New move: nature’s pledge

Type: grass (special)

PP: 10

95% accurate 60 base power. If used when both tancoon and Ranuki are on the field the power doubles.

*signature pokemon of the other champion tres*

summary: I went to ThinkTank Science Museum yesterday. It was honestly fascinating learning about the stars, the sun, human biology,...
body:
I went to ThinkTank Science Museum yesterday. It was honestly fascinating learning about the stars, the sun, human biology, animals. It was really interesting.

…I couldn’t get away from Pokémon though 😜. There was a section about epilepsy and its causes, so they put a Pikachu plush in there because of the impact Electric Soldier Porygon had.

There was also an engineering section there with everything from plug wiring to Minis. I genuinely love the look of classic cars. They have so much charm and character that modern cars lack. They’re better engineered and more practical, but… yeah, they’re mostly built for purpose rather than crafted.

I also loved the dummy locomotive prop they had there. It looked realistic and I could actually see inside the cab since the museum was completely accessible. Although it made me want to visit the National Railway Museum in York..!

I also saw this when I went into the city centre and the Bullring. It was fabulous. I was tempted to buy one, but decided against it.

Birmingham was really fun overall. It really tired me out, and I honestly slightly prefer Manchester for shopping purposes. But it was a nice change of pace and the museum was a real highlight.

I didn’t get to the gay village though, which is a shame. But I will get there the next time I’m around there.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

blog.name: inikavulpixelreviews
blog.title: Let's Talk About Pokemon!
blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Fennekin Family
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Fennekin Family
body:
653: Fennekin

…So if it’s not the Grass starter that is my favorite, which one is it this time then? It’s actually the Fire starter that’s my favorite! Starting with Fennekin here, which is another one of those Pokemon I just fell in love with instantly. It was cool to get a fennec fox! Big head to body ratio, with even bigger ears and everything. A warm and fluffy fire type! I certainly won’t say no to any of that.

I’m also fairly glad of two things here. One being that, despite us already having a fire fox, Fennekin is still plenty unique in look in its own right. And two being that the “dog” entry for fire type’s Zodiac theme is a fox. It’s a slight subversion to tackle another canid, which I’m more than fine with.

Fennekin though is simply too adorable, and it’s one of those Pokemon I simply love to death, despite me not having a ton to say about it. All I can do is admit that my gravitating toward these Fox Pokemon is entirely just out of selfish love for foxes. Like. Gamefreak would have to mess up to Lucario kinds of bad to get me to dislike a Fox Pokemon.

Personal Score: 10/10

Hhhhhhhhh FOX GOOD.

654: Braixen

But Braixen is just as, if not more fun than Fennekin is! Like any good Starter line lately, to plants the seeds of what’s to come. And to go with the DnD theme of Chesnaught, here we have Braixen slowly becoming a sorcerer! With a fun witch motif, including a cute little fur skirt and a stick it keeps in its tail, whipping it out to basically cast fire spells. What’s especially cool is that the stick in the tail even looks like a witch’s broomstick! All that’s really missing is some kind of proxy for a witch’s hat.

Out of all starter middle-evos, Braixen is easily my favorite not just because it manages to dodge the awkward teenager stage sort of look they mostly wind up having, but because it isn’t terribly stuck between trying to be cute but cool at the same time. It manages to capture a little bit of both as seamlessly as making an anthropomorphic fox and letting it twirl a wand around to cast fire spells. Also unlike a lot of middle-starter stages, this one’s got a cool visual motif to boot!

Also, y’all aughta know how I am about Halloween. And this can easily join the ranks of Mismagius and Murkrow as “cool witch Pokemon.”

Personal Score: 10/10

Hooray Halloween!

656: Delphox

Delphox I’m notably a bit less of a fan of. It’s still a cool fox, but Fennekin is cute and Braixen has the fun witch thing going on. Though Delphox still has plenty of room to stand on its own merits. My biggest turn-off is just the blunt introduction of the maroonish red. That and the legs being far less visible. Though that does contribute to the overall look. The personality of Delphox is just killing it, a really fun and elongated fox face with a conniving smirk. And it’s high time we got a Fire Starter that was anything but Fighting type. And what better way to break that mold than by making it a type that counters Fighting?

Indeed, as previously said, Delphox goes with the DnD class theme by becoming a Sorcerer or Mage! Now wielding a much longer stick wand. And it has long, flowing fur to copy the look of a wizard’s robe! Even down to the long and dangling sleeves, which it also keeps its new wand in. Not only that, but I’ve always thought the white fur going down its chest was also meant to look like a long, wizardy beard, too. Though that look would be fully realized had it been a continuous stripe down its chest. Again, all it’s really missing is a hat. But at least we can maybe see the giant ear-fuzz as some wiggy mage hair.

This wizard look is why I’ve always wondered what people meant when they said Delphox looks effeminate. Other than its attachment to Braixen of course. It’s not exactly Machamp but I’ve always seen more masculine traits in it than anything between that fake beard and robe-like fur.

Personal Score: 10/10

Still a 10/10, just not as much of a 10/10.

Overall:

A very good line of starters, that’s pretty much fantastic from beginning to end. Also the perfect Pokemon to cover for the Eve of October!
